==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pseudæsthesia
<hw>Pseu`d⟦ae⟧s*the"si*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Pseudo-</er>, and <er>aesthesia</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>False or imaginary feeling or sense
perception such as occurs in hypochondriasis, or such as is referred to
an organ that has been removed, as an amputated foot.</def><-- a phenom
also called phantom limbs -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudembryo</ent>⟦br⟧
